South Africa has now confirmed more than 4,500 COVID-19 infections and 87 deaths. Health Minister, Zweli Mkhize told Parliament's Portfolio Committee on Health today that the Western Cape has become the infection epicentre of the country. Courtesy #DStv403   CAPE TOWN - The DA wants the government to prioritise local healthcare professionals in the fight against COVID-19. South Africa has now confirmed more than 4,700 COVID-19 infections and 90 deaths. READ: Mkhize: COVID-19 patterns are changing On Monday, over 200 Cuban medical professionals landed in the country to join the fight against COVID-19. The team made up of doctors and specialists will be deployed across the country. READ: Cuban health professionals arrive in SA But DA MP Siviwe Gwarube said South African specialists and healthcare workers must be used to their capacity before relying on foreign aid that potentially comes at a cost. Gwarube said the party welcomes assistance from all corners but said local resources must be fully utilised. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.